trans-unit.source: Represents an ordered collection of <see cref="T:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding" /> objects.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma coleção ordenada de objetos de <see cref="T:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding" />.

trans-unit.source: All objects that derive from <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> have an <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> named <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.InputBindings%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Todos os objetos que derivam de <xref:System.Windows.UIElement> tem um <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> chamado <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.InputBindings%2A>.

trans-unit.source: All objects that derive from <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement> have an <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> named <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement.InputBindings%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Todos os objetos que derivam de <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement> tem um <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> chamado <xref:System.Windows.ContentElement.InputBindings%2A>.

trans-unit.source: However, if these collections are set in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], then the items in the collection must be derived classes of <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> rather than direct <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> objects.
trans-unit.target: No entanto, se essas coleções são definidas na [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)], em seguida, os itens na coleção devem ser classes derivadas de <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> em vez de direta <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> objetos.

trans-unit.source: This is because <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> does not support a default public constructor.
trans-unit.target: Isso ocorre porque <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> não oferece suporte a um construtor público padrão.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, the items in a <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> that was set in [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] will typically be an <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> derived class that does support a default public constructor, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyBinding> or <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding>.
trans-unit.target: Portanto, os itens em uma <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBindingCollection> que foi definida no [!INCLUDE[TLA2#tla_xaml](~/includes/tla2sharptla-xaml-md.md)] geralmente será um <xref:System.Windows.Input.InputBinding> derivado da classe que dá suporte a um construtor público padrão, como <xref:System.Windows.Input.KeyBinding> ou <xref:System.Windows.Input.MouseBinding>.
